title: Handbook of Food Factory Design
description:
Handbook of Food Factory Design by Christopher G. J. Baker

English | ISBN: 1461474493 | 2013 | PDF | 499 pages | 6,5 MB

Food manufacturing has evolved over the centuries from kitchen industries to modern, sophisticated production operations. A typical food factory includes the food processing and packaging lines, the buildings and exterior landscaping, and the utility-supply and waste-treatment facilities
